# MootsKeeper

MootsKeeper is a lightweight relationship manager for streamers and VTubers to track moots, collab context, and social links in one place.

## Live Project
- App: https://mootskeeper.com

## Who It’s For
- Streamers and VTubers managing lots of mutuals/collab contacts
- Creators who want quick memory support for names, vibes, links, and availability

## Current Features
- Twitch and Google sign-in
- Contact CRUD (create, edit, delete, organize)
- Relationship labels and keyword/tag workflows
- Social link fields per contact
- User preferences persistence (onboarding + account-side settings groundwork)
- Side panel tools for fast navigation

## Project Status
Active development.  
Core functionality is usable now; quality-of-life and account features are still being expanded.

## Roadmap
- Native MootsKeeper account registration (username/password)
- Public discoverability toggle + user lookup suggestions
- Expanded settings modal
- More workflow tools in side panel (reminders, quick notes, etc.)

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
- Backend: FastAPI (Python)
- Database: PostgreSQL
- Hosting: Railway + static frontend hosting

## Local Development (WIP docs)
Local setup instructions will be expanded as the project stabilizes.

## Privacy Note
MootsKeeper stores only data required to provide account and contact-management features.  
Please avoid storing sensitive personal information in notes/tags.

